## When Working Across Multiple Repos

1. Read `medinovai.manifest.yaml` in each repo first — understand its tier, squad, dependencies.
2. Check `docs/PRODUCTION_REPO_ROUTING_MAP.md` in `medinovai-Developer` to confirm the right repo for each capability.
3. Never write production code in `medinovai-Developer` — it is reference only.
4. Cross-repo changes must update the event bus contract in `medinovai-real-time-stream-bus` if new events are introduced.
5. Any new API must have an OpenAPI contract in `medinovai-Developer/data-contracts/` before implementation.
6. Apply the 5-iteration recursive quality loop before sign-off on regulated features.
